# Code patterns (copy these)

## Adding a new API route

File: `api/src/routes/v1/<resource>.ts`. Register it in `api/src/routes/v1/index.ts`.

```typescript
import type { FastifyPluginAsync } from "fastify";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { db } from "../../db/client.js";
import { broadcastInvalidate } from "../../lib/realtime-bus.js";
import { myTable } from "../../db/schema.js";
import { uuidParam, createMyBody } from "../../schemas/api.js";

export const myRoutes: FastifyPluginAsync = async (app) => {
  app.get("/my-things", async () => {
    const rows = await db.select().from(myTable);
    return { myThings: rows };
  });

  app.post("/my-things", async (req, reply) => {
    const body = createMyBody.parse(req.body);
    const [row] = await db.insert(myTable).values(body).returning();
    broadcastInvalidate([["myThings"]]);        // <-- REQUIRED for SSE
    req.log.debug({ id: row.id }, "thing created"); // <-- REQUIRED logging
    return reply.code(201).send({ myThing: row });
  });
};
```

Key rules:
- Parse params/body with **Zod** (`schemas/api.ts` or local).
- Call **`broadcastInvalidate`** after every successful mutation.
- Log with **`req.log.debug`** (never `console.log`).
- Return `{ resourceName: row }` (match existing responses).

## Adding Zod schemas

File: `api/src/schemas/api.ts` for shared schemas. Local schemas are fine for route-specific validation.

## Adding a new frontend page

1. Create `web/src/pages/MyPage.tsx`.
2. Add a `<Route>` in `web/src/App.tsx` inside the `<AuthGate>` wrapper.
3. Use `useQuery` with a **`queryKey`** that matches what the API's `broadcastInvalidate` sends.

```tsx
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { apiGet } from "../api/client";

export function MyPage() {
  const q = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["myThings"],       // must match broadcastInvalidate key
    queryFn: () => apiGet<{ myThings: MyThing[] }>("/api/v1/my-things"),
  });

  if (q.isLoading) return <p className="muted">Loadingā€¦</p>;
  if (q.error || !q.data) return <p role="alert">Failed to load.</p>;
  // render q.data.myThings
}
```

## Adding a frontend mutation

```tsx
import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from "@tanstack/react-query";

const qc = useQueryClient();
const mut = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (body: CreateBody) =>
    apiSend("/api/v1/my-things", "POST", body),
  onSuccess: () => qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["myThings"] }),
});
```

Use `apiSend` (JSON) or `apiSendForm` (multipart) from `web/src/api/client.ts`.

## CSS and styling

- **All tokens** live in `web/src/global.css` (`:root[data-theme]` selectors).
- Use `var(--color-*)`, `var(--radius-*)` ā€” never hardcode `#hex` colors or `8px` radii.
- Available tokens: `--color-bg`, `--color-surface`, `--color-border`, `--color-text`, `--color-text-muted`, `--color-brand`, `--color-on-brand`, `--color-overlay`.
- Use `.card`, `.muted`, `.title-bar`, `button.primary` classes ā€” don't recreate them.
- No CSS modules ā€” everything is in `global.css`.
- FortuneSheet CSS is imported in `main.tsx` before `global.css`.

## Compact action buttons (match stage day)

Use the same pattern as **`StageDayPage`** performance rows (**Patch / RF**, **Files**, **Notes**, **Swap**):

- **`button.icon-btn`** or **`a.icon-btn`** with a **short text label** (not emoji-only controls mixed with plain text links).
- Default **`font-size: 0.8rem`** for `button.icon-btn` is in **`global.css`**; **`a.icon-btn`** already sets **`0.8rem`**.
- **Danger** actions: `button.icon-btn.danger-text` with a text label (e.g. **Delete**).

Do **not** use a raw `<a>` without **`icon-btn`** next to **`icon-btn`** buttons ā€” it breaks visual alignment. See **`docs/DEVELOPMENT.md`** ā†’ *UI: compact action buttons*.

## File types

- Add shared frontend types to `web/src/api/types.ts`.
- API response shapes should match: `{ resourceName: Row }` for single, `{ resourceNames: Row[] }` for lists.

## File attachments (`/api/v1/files`)

- **List:** `GET /api/v1/files?stageId=` (stage-only files) or `?performanceId=` (per-band files).
- **Upload:** `POST /api/v1/files?stageId=` **or** `?performanceId=` ā€” multipart field `file` only; new rows are stored as **`generic`** (Other). **PATCH** `purpose` to **`rider_pdf`** or **`plot_pdf`** as needed. Allowed types: see `api/src/lib/upload-allowlists.ts` (PDF, images, text, common docs).
- **Extract:** `POST /api/v1/files/:id/extract-page` JSON `{ "pageIndex": 0 }` (0-based) ā€” **PDF sources only**.
- **Convert to PDF:** `POST /api/v1/files/:id/convert-to-pdf` ā€” creates a **new** `file_assets` row (`application/pdf`, **`generic`**), **`parentFileId`** set to the source; **ImageMagick** / **LibreOffice** / **pdf-lib** (`api/src/lib/convert-to-pdf.ts`). List/get responses include **`canConvertToPdf`** when the source can be converted.
- **TanStack keys:** `["files", stageId]` and `["files", "performance", performanceId]` ā€” must be invalidated after upload/delete/extract/convert (see `api/src/routes/v1/files.ts`).
